                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <head>164. Telegram From the Department of State to the Embassy in Iran<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d164fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1950–1954, 788.11/2–2753.
                        Top Secret; Security Information; Limited Distribution; Priority. Drafted by
                            <persName corresp="#p_SJHJ_1">Stutesman</persName> and approved by
                            <persName corresp="#p_RAL_1">Richards</persName>. Repeated to
                        London.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1953-02-27T17:43:00-05:00">February 27, 1953, 5:43
                    p.m</date>.</dateline>
                <p>2238. In view Shah’s apparent desire leave Iran and <persName corresp="#p_MM_1"
                        >Mosadeq</persName>’s position that Shah should leave, Department sees
                    little which could usefully be done to prevent Shah’s departure. We are
                    currently assessing significance this crisis and developments likely flow from
                    Shah’s departure, and would appreciate any comments you may have in
                    amplification <gloss target="#t_urtel_1">urtel</gloss> 3397<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d164fn2">
                        <ref target="#d162">Document 162</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_rpt_1">rpt</gloss> London 1103. Department will attempt
                    minimize to press significance Shah’s departure Iran but there is every
                    likelihood press will take line that Shah has fled Iran and his case is similar
                    to Farouk’s.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Dulles</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
